Yercaud was how spring is, blissful and colourful. The whimsical curvy and narrow roads carpeted with blossoms changed colours from Gulmohar’s red to Jacaranda’s purple to Royal Poinciana’s yellow as we drove through the hillocks. 💮
.
.
Escape to this tiny town in Tamil Nadu was motivated by one thought alone, #focusontheweekend . All we craved for was a long drive, away from the daily hustle and into the lap of nature. A trip solely curated to align with our innate being; and the destination embraced us with open arms and empty roads. ⛰️
.
.
I remember we were driving to a coffee plantation in the neighbourhood when we passed through this scenic pathway. The view arrested our attention instantly, making us take yet another halt and simply stroll and gaze at the popping purple around us. 🚶‍♀️
.
.
📸 escapetolandscapes 🌈
.
.

Satin... un tessuto fluido, mordido e sensuale che scivola come una carezza sul tuo corpo senza segnarlo.

Perfetto in quelle situazioni dove è richiesto un outfit elegante.

Ma se vuoi dare uno stile più rock al tuo outfit, la scelta degli abbinamenti e degli accessori, diventa di fondamentale importanza!

Ekaya's Spring Summer 23 collection refines and redefines the house codes of craft, innovation and novelty. Underscoring freewheeling suppleness and rekindling the magic of heritage Petit point embroidery, each ensemble packs a vibrant punch. This season, Ekaya's atelier trains focus on the dexterously executed Petit point embroidery (a derivative of cross-stitch embroidery technique, but even finer), which can be traced back to 17th and 18th century France. Imbued with whimsy, sentiment and romance, this collection brings into play a luscious palette of azure blue, powder pink, ivory, cream and buttercup yellow. An artistic accumulation and exchange of the Petit Point embroidery is mixed with stripes, gingham and polka dots that tricks the eye. More on Digital Platform.

The Lady of the Argosaronic Gulf. 

The island is a popular destination because of its monuments, grand houses, museums, and cosmopolitan ambiance. A car-free destination including tasty dishes in the local tavernas, great views, architecture and orthodox churches. It is appreciated by celebrities such as M. Callas, P. Picasso, M. Loren, etc. 

Hydra's settlers came from the Peloponnese mainland few miles away, after the Ottoman invasion of the region. Following up on the collapse of the despotate of the Morea (1460), and the Orloff's failure against the Turks Uprising (1770), many Arvanites had migrated to the island. The Hydrians, thanks to their seamanship (Miaoulis Andreas), piracy, and merchant, greatly contributed to the nation's rebellion against the Ottomans.

The jaali or lattice work is a type of ornamental perforated screen that is commonly used in traditional Indian architecture. It is typically made of stone or marble and features intricate geometric patterns or floral motifs. The jaali serves many purposes, including providing ventilation and light, privacy, and protection from the elements. Today, it is still used in architecture and interior design to add a touch of traditional Indian elegance to modern spaces.

Se la grande Loredana Berté cantava "Questo vento agita anche me", noi in Salone scriviamo "Questo vento agita anche i tuoi capelli..". Come sempre, ascoltiamo e osserviamo ciò che ci accade intorno e ne traiamo ispirazioni professionali. Ormai sapete bene che a Casa StilNovo non esiste Bellezza senza Cura e infatti, anche oggi, desideriamo ricordarvi di proteggere la vostra chioma in base alle condizioni atmosferiche. Questi sono giorni di grande vento, soffia senza sosta e modifica le caratteristiche dell'aria. La tendenza più comune è quella della secchezza, pertanto, un protettore del capello consigliato dal vostro Consulente, così come uno styling raccolto ma non troppo tirato, potrebbero essere due semplici antidoti all'increspatura da vento. Per le amanti dei cappelli, non dimenticate che volano via quindi, una berretta in cotone con una coda bassa e un paio di occhiali da sole, sono un consiglio che coniuga protezione e stile in maniera facilmente praticabile. E ultima cosa, ma non in termini di importanza, spazzolate sempre e comunque i capelli, anche se sono arruffati ma prima di farlo, utilizzate un Conditioner Leave-In e un pettine a denti larghi in legno, esercitando un brushing delicato e discendente, facendo aderire una mano sulla testa mentre districate le lunghezze. Ma ciò che non dovreste mai dimenticare è di prevenire la secchezza delle lunghezze e le irritazioni della cute che in questo periodo si fanno sentire con insistenza, come accade in tutti i cambi stagionali. Noi da domani vi aspettiamo in Salone per prenderci cura di voi. I nostri numeri: 0543 705164 oppure 366 9282186.
Perché un Consulente StilNovo è per sempre..

Launching the “Chaukara Sari”

Gujarati style of making Checks pattern on a Brocade ground surface (fabric/fragment), The silk ground is divided into Large squares or “Chaukaras” or “Charkhanas” that has floral or Fauna Motifs, predominantly a 4 petel bilateral Flower (Champa/Champaca) or the quintessential Peacock Buta (very popular in Gujarat brocade weaving).

  Charkhana Patterns were very popular amongst the north central Indian royalties in the mid-19th century for its extravagant Visual Elegance and graphical beauty. The repetitive Characteristic of this particular Karigari is a visual delight and soothes the eye like a symmetrical synergistic rhythm. 
Also very popular and prominent, shown in the woven fabrics of the Jain traditions and Gujarati or western Indian paintings, Charkhana is one of those rare Textile beauties we adore

Primavera: colori di tendenza⁣👚
 ⁣
E’ sicuramente tra le mie stagioni preferite: non poteva esser diversamente, una che ama indossare colori pastello anche d’inverno (poco niente nero!)
 ⁣
Parlando di capi d’abbigliamento,avete già dato un’occhiata a quali saranno i colori di tendenza per la primavera estate?⁣
⁣
📌Eccovi le 5 nuance più cool e ricercate:⁣
 ⁣
🌼Rosa pesca: YEAH. Basta usarlo solo per le cerimonie!!!E’ tra le nuance di punta di questa stagione da abbinare in qualsiasi look⁣
🌼Verde acido: una versione più acida del classico prato, più squillante ed intensa, da mixare con accessori neri, viola o marroni
🌼Nude: un non colore, il beige. Io non lo amo particolarmente ma abbronzata potrei farcela …Il segreto di styling è sceglierlo il più simile possibile al proprio skin tone⁣
🌼Argento: questo pantone metallizzato torna a far parlare di sè grazie al suo nuovo appeal elegante. Scelto tanto per gli abiti da sera più sbrilluccicanti, quanto di giorno accostato al bianco, rosa, nero e altre tonalità basic⁣
🌼Blu Klein: è stata l’artista francese Yves Klein che decise di usare questa precisa punta di blu per le proprie opere. E’ un colore versatile e facile da indossare, perfetto per i tailleur che l’abbigliamento più casual⁣
⁣
👉Guarda tutte le foto sulle stories: dimmi quale di questi 5 colori indosserai sicuramente?⁣

📸💛 Basanto kalin durgotsob 💛📸

King Surath and Boishyo (Vaisya) Samadhi worshipped Devi Durga as Durga Puja or Durgotsob (Bengali: দুর্গোৎসব) at the ashram of Medhas Muni in the Garh Jungle of West Bengal. It was the first durgapuja of world. In current days, the ghar jungle is in Durgapur, Purba Bardhaman, West bengal. They worshipped Devi durga in spring time. So, this festival is called Basanti puja (Bengali: বাসন্তী পূজা). 🧿

🌸 MISS DIOR 🌸 

🌸Hello mes beauties,  le printemps est là!!Savez-vous que c'est ma saison favorite ? Eh bien maintenant vous le savez!😉 #springiscoming

🌸Je vous ai partagé mes favoris parfums dernièrement,  oui je suis une addict des parfums , aujourd'hui je reviens avec un de mes parfums favoris avec une marque que j'apprécie énormément je veux bien sûr parlé de dior ❤️❤️ avec la nouvelle eau de parfum Miss Dior.

🌸Fleuries et fraîches, les notes olfactives de Miss Dior sont composées comme un bouquet de mille fleurs aux mille couleurs chatoyantes : François Demachy, le Parfumeur-Créateur de la maison Dior, a voulu pour cette fragrance créer une rose iridescente illuminée par une myriade de touches fraîches et florales.

🌸Le nœud couture iconique de Miss Dior, fort d'un exceptionnel savoir-faire artisanal qui transforme chaque ruban brodé en pièce unique, est une véritable création de haute couture.
🌸Note de tête : Les notes d'un muguet à la floralité fraîche, l'accord de pivoine expressive et les notes d'iris caressant accompagnent une belle verdeur un peu mouillée.

🌸Notes de cœur : Une rose veloutée, charnue et délicieusement onctueuse, autour de laquelle une brassée pareille à un « millefiori » prend vie.

🌸Notes de fond : Des muscs ouatés, une touche de vanille de Papouasie Nouvelle Guinée, une pointe de benjoin et un soupçon de fève Tonka à la rencontre d'un santal crémeux.

🌸Un vrai parfum pour les beaux jours, très fleurie et son packaging très élégant rappelle la finesse et l'élégance un vrai bonheur !!

🌸Et vous mes beauties, quel est votre parfum favoris?? Dites-moi tous ça en commentaires lâchez vous !!🥰

A los 40 aprendí que no puedes gustarle a todo el mundo como si fueses chocolate...
pero que lo importante es caerte bien a ti mismo
 y ser feliz con tu mecanismo...

Que  te equivocarás y tropezarás...
Pero que de tanto hacerlo ya caes
 y te levantas con estilo...

Que quizás tú tableta de chocolate y tú perfect culamen ya no son tan perfectos
 pero tu corazón es más bonico 
a cada ratito...

Que a veces tenemos que perdernos para encontrarnos...
pero como dice mi madre...ningún perdido se pierde
 y donde sientes que es hogar siempre vuelves...

Que si la vida mal,puedes resetearte una y mil veces
 y empezar a escribir un nuevo cuento 
que te ponga el ❤️ más contento...

Que la felicidad depende de uno mismo porque es con quién coincides 24/7 
pero siempre ayuda ese amig@ 
que hace tus carcajadas más sonoras 

Que algo pequeño puede ilusionarte a lo grande...
porque sino hablamos de un glande,
el tamaño no es importante 

Que nunca es tarde para sentir mariposas en el clítoris con tu Crush ..
sino que se lo digan a J.Lo y a Ben Afleck

Que al final siempre hacemos cagadas espaciales pero incluso esas nos traen momentos especiales...

Os deseo una noche genial 
y que si lo necesitas mañana empieces de cero
sintiendote un 10

The magic of Banarasi silk saree is inspired by the Mughals. Golden and silver Zaris are used to weave the designs of flowers and motifs. Launching the “Chaukara Sari”

Gujarati style of making Checks pattern on a Brocade ground surface (fabric/fragment), The silk ground is divided into Large squares or “Chaukaras” or “Charkhanas” that has floral or Fauna Motifs, predominantly a 4 petel bilateral Flower (Champa/Champaca) or the quintessential Peacock Buta (very popular in Gujarat brocade weaving).

  Charkhana Patterns were very popular amongst the north central Indian royalties in the mid-19th century for its extravagant Visual Elegance and graphical beauty. The repetitive Characteristic of this particular Karigari is a visual delight and soothes the eye like a symmetrical synergistic rhythm. 
Also very popular and prominent, shown in the woven fabrics of the Jain traditions and Gujarati or western Indian paintings, Charkhana is one of those rare Textile beauties we adore

L.B.M.1911は、100年以上の歴史をもつ　　　　　　イタリアンラグジュアリーブランド
「ルビアム」のカジュアルライン。

ブランド名「L.B.M.1911」は、それぞれ創業者 Luigi、Bianchi、と創業地 Mantovaの頭文字を取り、さらに創業年の”1911”を組み合わせています。
 
多くのブランドが製造を他の工場に外注している昨今において、創業初期から変わらずマントヴァの工場で製造している数少ない自社生産ブランドです。

Riz et rais
Lorsque l’orange lumineux donne le rythme. Et trace la voie : c’est bien lui qui pare le mocassin blanc Comael d’un supplément de raffinement féminin. Et lui encore qui réchauffe l’atmosphère épurée du café Koji Saryo, conçu par les architectes Atsushi Suzuki et Transit Branding Studio. Installé dans un complexe commercial du district de Taki, au Japon, région de montagne et de fortes précipitations de neige, son ambiance graphique éclairée y est directement inspirée du koji, procédé de fermentation du riz grâce auquel fabriquer l’Amazake, boisson traditionnelle star de l’endroit.

-

Of rice and (wo)men
When bright orange sets the tone… And leads the way, adorning our white Comael moccasins with added feminine refinement. The colour also creates a warm, uncluttered setting at café Koji Saryo, designed by architects Atsushi Suzuki and Transit Branding Studio. Situated in a shopping centre in Japan’s Taki district — a mountainous region with heavy rain- and snowfall, the sunny graphic atmosphere draws its inspiration from koji, a rice fermentation process used to produce Amazake, a traditional beverage that is the star of the show here.

BAGGAGE/ SS24
.
.
The Baggage collection is inspired by the idea of carrying something with you, whether it’s a tangible object or an intangible emotion, that holds the ability to weigh you down. 
The collection blends the concept of emotional baggage with the physicality of carrying a tangible bag, expressing elements of personal history and emotional experiences through oversized cuts, heavy fabrics, thread art, and layered shoulders.
The collection is designed to offer a medium for individuals to express their emotions through fashion. It features functional elements such as pockets, pouches, and straps, drawing inspiration from the physical attributes of a carry bag. The collection showcases how our personal experiences and identities are reflected in our style and fashion choices.
Overall, the Baggage collection offers a unique perspective on the intersection between personal experiences and fashion, encouraging individuals to explore their emotions and express themselves through clothing
.

🇬🇧 Portuguese Book Day
This day was created to celebrate and highlight the importance of books, but also of the Portuguese language, throughout the world.

One of the best known books is "Os Lusíadas" by Luís Vaz de Camões, about the time of the Portuguese discoveries. And possibly the best known Portuguese writer is José Saramago, Nobel Prize in Literature in 1998, the only Nobel in this category to date.

Have you read a little today?

🇫🇷 Journée du Livre Portugais

Cette journée a été créée afin de célébrer et souligner l’importance des livres, mais aussi de la langue portugaise, dans le monde entier.

L’un des livres de la littérature portugaise le plus connu est "Os Lusíadas (Les lusiades)" de Luis Vaz de Camões, sur l’époque des découvertes portugaises. 
Et l’écrivain portugais le plus connu est peut-être José Saramago, Nobel de littérature, en 1998, le seul Nobel de cette catégorie à ce jour.

Avez-vous lu aujourd’hui ?

🇵🇹 Dia do Livro Português
Este dia foi criado com o intuito de celebrar e destacar a importância dos livros, mas também da língua portuguesa, em todo o mundo.

Um dos livros mais conhecidos é “Os Lusíadas” de Luís Vaz de Camões, sobre a época dos descobrimentos portugueses. E, possivelmente, o escritor português mais conhecido é José Saramago, Nobel da Literatura, em 1998, o único Nobel nesta categoria até aos dias de hoje.

Já leu um pouco hoje?
